As a part of Amadeus Hospitality & Media Distribution, travel audience is the world’s leading data-driven travel advertising platform. The business unit harnesses the power of cutting-edge machine learning practices to connect the leading performance-oriented advertisers with the biggest network of publishers, reaching millions of travellers. The strategy is to optimize advertising across the entire traveller journey, identify and create new audiences, and increase our partners reach, relevance and booking volumes.

We are looking for a Junior Data Analyst to join our Data Tribe. You’ll be part of a team that is disrupting the industry with innovative attribution models and building the future analytics platform to be used by DMOs worldwide for campaign performance and market insights. You’ll be working on very exciting projects using BigQuery, Composer, Tableau, all cloud-based solutions, and with terabytes of data coming from different sources.
What you'll do:
You'll learn the several data sets at the company's disposal and how to use them in a meaningful manner
You'll build and maintain visually appealing and engaging dashboards for external customers and internal stakeholders;
You'll support the team with data analysis requests from the different stakeholders
You'll learn about our best practices and how to master Tableau, BigQuery and other tools and processes in use by the team;
You'll present data and insights in a clear manner with actionable outputs to the team and internal stakeholders.

About you:
You enjoy managing people and you have done it successfully before;
You enjoy coaching, mentoring and developing team and individual’s skills;
You have used in significant capacity multiple programming languages covering different paradigms;
You have successfully built robust user-facing systems;
You have significant API design and architecture experience;
You know how to facilitate discussions and communicate with different stakeholders;
You care about engineering quality and know how it can be achieved;
You can speak, write and express yourself in English – our company’s working language – in a professional context.

Why join us?
As part of our team, you will work in a highly motivated environment, with equal opportunities, flat hierarchies and short decision-making processes. You'll have a lot of freedom to contribute your own ideas and implement them. You will be a part of a diverse team with a strong sense of ownership that always goes beyond to make an impact while constantly learning and being truly passionate about Travel.
Drive innovation and develop tech solutions that bring value to our customers, and to make an impact on both the business and the market;
Join a fast-paced industry which is evolving every day while being backed by Amadeus, the biggest travel tech company in the world;
Be a part of an innovative environment where you are encouraged to research, explore, and try new ways of doing things;
Learn and develop – we offer personalised approach to your development that combines a wide range of tools and programs, such as mentoring and coaching;
Enjoy your work-life balance – we provide Urban Sports Club membership, sabbatical options, certified experts in mental health and many more;
We got you covered - we offer visa and relocation support and assist you on other location-related topics along your journey with us;
Pick your hardware – we will set you up with the equipment you select for your daily working needs;
Smooth start - our extensive onboarding program and regular Team events facilitate your integration into our culture;
Make the most of our Travel perks - we offer travel insurance for you and your family, and a travel industry card with lots of benefits to explore;
Share company’s success – we offer a competitive bonus scheme, and a stock purchase options that every member can participate in.
At travel audience, we do not make hiring or employment decisions based on race, color, religion or religious belief, ethnic or national origin, nationality, sex, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, age or any other basis protected by applicable laws or prohibited by company policy. As an Equal Opportunity Employer, we celebrate diversity and create a healthy environment based on mutual respect and care.

We are eagerly awaiting your application and looking forward to starting our journey together!
